<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="439" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,649,964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,649,675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamiya" authorityName="Kamiya" box="[537,694,649,676]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rai">
<emphasis box="[537,600,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">A. rai</emphasis>
Kamiya
</taxonomicName>
in male genitalia but can be separated from the latter by the entirely brown elytra without dark brown markings on humeral and apical parts (
<figureCitation box="[951,1032,685,712]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
). It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Peng et Chen" authorityName="Peng et Chen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongxinensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1260,1436,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">A. gongxinensis</emphasis>
Peng et Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[312,371,722,748]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in external appearance, but can be recognized by the different shape of the abdominal postcoxal lines (
<figureCitation box="[219,300,757,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
) and penis guide in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[674,754,757,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,649,964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,793,819]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,793,820]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.595" metricValueMax="1.62" metricValueMin="1.57" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" unit="mm" value="1.595" valueMax="1.62" valueMin="1.57">1.57–1.62 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,793,820]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.06" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" unit="mm" value="1.08" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="1.06">1.06–1.10 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,793,820]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" unit="mm" value="0.77" valueMax="0.78" valueMin="0.76">0.76–0.78 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.47–1.49, EL/EW: 1.08– 1.17, PL/PW: 0.52–0.57, HW/PW: 0.70–0.72, PW/EW: 0.66–0.68.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,649,964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">
Body oval, weekly convex, dorsum with pale yellow pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[945,1059,865,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Figs 5a–c</figureCitation>
). Head dark brown, antennae and mouthparts yellow, tip of mandibles brown. Pronotum yellow, scutellar shield dark brown. Elytra dark brown. Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum yellow. Mesoventrite and metaventrite dark brown. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" startId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" targetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1918,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ren et Pang, 1992" authorityName="Ren et Pang" authorityYear="1992" box="[284,720,1919,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glotticus">
<emphasis box="[284,523,1919,1943]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Axinoscymnus glotticus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, S. X. &amp; Pang, X. F." box="[531,720,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" pagination="20 - 23" refId="ref16694" refString="Ren, S. X. &amp; Pang, X. F. (1992) The Axinoscymnus Kamiya (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) from China. Coccinella, 4, 20 - 23." type="journal article" year="1992">Ren et Pang, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[727,843,1918,1942]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">(Holotype)</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[857,870,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">a</emphasis>
dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1018,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">b</emphasis>
lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1164,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">c</emphasis>
frontal view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1303,1317,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">d</emphasis>
abdomen 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1425,1436,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">e</emphasis>
penis 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,219,1954,1978]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">f</emphasis>
tegmen, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,451,1955,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">g</emphasis>
tegmen, inner view 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[658,672,1955,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">h</emphasis>
labels of holotype. Scale bars: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[990,1035,1955,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">a–c:</emphasis>
0.5 mm, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1131,1154,1955,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">d:</emphasis>
0.1 mm, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1250,1295,1955,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">e–g:</emphasis>
0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
Head with fine and sparse frontal punctures, 2.0–2.5 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.33 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[528,612,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Fig. 5c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures similar with those on frons. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching 3/4 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1368,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with coarse and irregular punctures at middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
Male genitalia. Penis short and slender, slightly broadened at base, apex pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1124,1206,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Fig. 5e</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide subtrapezoidal, parallel sided at basal 1/4, then strongly tapering to apex in inner view (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1307,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1277,1307,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" unit="g" value="5.0">5g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), about 3/4 length of parameres; parameres stout and elongate oval with few setae at apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1287,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
